BEGIN_PGML
A rectangular prism's base area can be calculated by the formula [`B=\frac{V}{h}\text{,}`] where [`V`] is the volume and [`h`] is the height.

A certain rectangular prism's volume can be modeled by [`[$v]`] cubic units. If its height is [`[$h]`] units, find the prism's base area.

[_]{$ans}{16}

END_PGML

############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
Using the formula,

[```B=\frac{[$v]}{[$h]}```]

Now we can divide [`[$h]`] into each of the three terms in the numerator. So the base area is modeled by [`[$ans]\text{.}`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

